article.headline: TCU 89, Angelo St. 70
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Brent Hackett scored 19 points and Alvardo Parker added 18 to lead TCU past Angelo State 89-70 Saturday night. Hackett and Parker sparked a 16-3 run in the second half which stretched TCU's lead to 15 in the second half in its season opener. Angelo State's Marcus Hubbard scored 17 points and Nathan Walton chipped in with 13. The Horned Frogs led just 44-42 early in the second half before they took over. Parker scored six and Hackett had five in a run that put TCU on top 58-43 with 14:46 left. Hackett hit a 3-pointer to cap the spurt. TCU's Henry Salter scored all 13 of his points in the second half.
